  "texts": [
    "Statistically efficient: Our judges are based on GLMs, which can be learned from limited data.",
    "This is expected in most applications of our work.",
    "Our judges are designed such that the base judge's score or a distribution of it serves as a bias term in our model.",
    "This allows us, at least in principle, to always learn at least as good judges as the base judge.",
    "Computationally efficient: Learning of classic machine learning models on the top of frozen LLM embeddings is more computationally efficient, and can also be more statistically efficient, than fine-tuning."
  ],
